social_posts.post_text: Merry Christmas 🎄

The end of the year means time for “Reflection.” Love it or hate it. This philosophy is really critical to a business as a whole and it gives continuous improvement. I had soooooooo much fun this year. I made myself get comfortable in front of the camera and be much more vulnerable as a person. I honestly love the growth I had as a mom, wife , friend, and business owner. I truly can’t wait to get back to what I love most.. creating. Thank you ! (( in bad bunny’s voice .. 2023 viene carbon)
92 magical booked sessions🖤 I  am grateful for every moment I was able to create for every single beautiful woman that walked into my studio 🖤 THANK YOU ! To my 2023 sessions, can’t wait to see you !

Mama Marisa 🖤

#miamiphotographer #miami #maternityreel #maternityphotos #fineart #hialeahphotographer #miamimaternity #browardmaternityphotographer #studiophoto #motherhoodphoto #mommyandme #motherhoodphotography #miamimom

You abandon your business social media for 3 months. 

I’m backkkk ! Took a very much needed and wanted mental and personal break. It was amazing to just disconnect from my creative mind without any stressors and new photography trends. I felt amazing to just see new techniques and styles popping out and feeling like I didn’t need to jump on that wagon. I’m content with my disconnect and not worry I’m being left behind in the photography world. Plus, I was able to enjoy my family and holidays because lord knows the moment Halloween hits.. everything is chaos. 

Did I do anything I planned  during the break ? Absolutely NOT! 

Do I regret not doing what I planned? Maybe a little

Do I second guess my decision? Not an ounce 

Am I excited to be back full throttle with sessions ! HELLLLL YEAH !! 

2023 is starting off bien cabron 🤸🏽‍♀️

Toddlers🤍 

Let’s talk these full of character and energy kiddos. Is it hard during a session ? In my opinion.. they are the hardest to capture. Running a small business can be a challenging experience, but it is also incredibly rewarding. 💕

As a small business owner, you have to wear many hats and juggle numerous responsibilities, including managing finances, marketing your brand, and providing exceptional customer service. It’s easy to feel overwhelmed and want to give up when faced with obstacles and setbacks. 😵‍💫

However, it’s important to remember that every successful entrepreneur has faced similar struggles and overcome them. The key is to stay focused on your goals and keep pushing through the difficult times🤸🏽‍♀️🤸🏽‍♀️. With perseverance and determination, you can achieve your dreams and build a thriving business. 

So, don’t give up on your entrepreneurial aspirations - 🖤the journey may be tough, but the rewards are well worth it.🖤

✨Embracing Tiger Stripes, the beautiful truth 🐅✨

When a handful of clients walk in and say, 'Let's keep my marks untouched,' my heart does a happy dance!  Stretch marks often get a bad rap during pregnancy, but have you ever stopped tothinj about their significance? These marks tell a story of growth and transformation, a journey worth celebrating and loving. 🫶🏻

 Mama Lucia! ✨ Do marks define her? Absolutely not. They're a testament of courage and self-love, a reminder that embracing our unique journey is a beautiful thing. So here's to embracing every part of ourselves, and to smiling through it all! 😊✨🫶🏻#EmbraceYourJourney #TigerStripes #SelfLove"
